Virgin’s Licensing Unit to Move to Geneva, Telegraph Reports

-- B y   N a m i t h a   J a g a d e e s h
-- 
2011-07-26T22:03:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/virgin-s-licensing-unit-to-move-to-geneva-telegraph-reports.html
Virgin Group plans to move Virgin
Enterprise, the unit that owns the rights to the Virgin brand
globally, to Geneva, the  Daily Telegraph  reported, citing a
person with knowledge of the matter.  The move is intended to increase “tax efficiency,” the
Telegraph cited the person as saying. A spokesman for Virgin
confirmed that part of the business would be moving to
 Switzerland , the newspaper said.  -- Editor: John Simpson  To contact the reporter on this story:
